    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-06T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="80"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d80">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">850.33/8–652: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 80<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France (<persName corresp="#p_ACHILLESTC1"
                            type="from">Achilles</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-06T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 6, 1952—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>823. ReDeptel 567<note n="1" xml:id="d80fn1">
                        <ref target="#d76">Document 76</ref>.</note> and <gloss target="#t_Torep1"
                        >Torep</gloss> 569.<note n="2" xml:id="d80fn2">
                        <ref target="#d77">Document 77</ref>.</note> In agreement with <persName
                        corresp="#p_DRAPERWHJ1">Draper</persName>, am sending <persName
                        corresp="#p_TOMLINSONWM1">Tomlinson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CLEVELANDSM1">Stanley Cleveland</persName> to Luxembourg
                    temporarily <pb facs="0197" n="149" xml:id="pg_149"/> to cover <persName
                        corresp="#p_SCHUMANR1">Schuman</persName> Plan developments beginning August
                    10. They may be accompanied by one or more members of <gloss target="#t_SRE1"
                        >SRE</gloss> staff. Believe this arrangement will serve temporarily to keep
                    all interested US agencies adequately informed and provide channel for US
                    contact with high authority.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_MERCHANTLT1">Merchant</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_TOMLINSONWM1">Tomlinson</persName>, who is flying Washington
                    tonight, fully familiar with situation. In conversation with <persName
                        corresp="#p_MONNETJ1">Monnet</persName> yesterday (which <persName
                        corresp="#p_DRAPERWHJ1">Draper</persName> reporting) was struck by <persName
                        corresp="#p_MONNETJ1">Monnet</persName>’s calm and pragmatic approach to
                    development of high authority, which he plans to keep small and develop only as
                    its functional needs become clear in practice. Believe we would be well advised
                    to follow same course; i.e., to follow development of high authority closely,
                    but defer setting up special mission, particularly large or high level one,
                    until concrete needs of US representation become more clear.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ACHILLESTC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Achilles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
